GANGDONG INTERNATIONAL MEDICAL CENTER

22
00:03:21,285 --> 00:03:23,245
SEVEN HOURS EARLIER

23
00:03:23,725 --> 00:03:25,725
TIANYI MEDIA &amp; CULTURE CO.

24
00:03:29,285 --> 00:03:30,165
Is this my driver?

25
00:03:31,525 --> 00:03:33,085
Yes, I'm at the entrance of Tianyi.

26
00:03:35,565 --> 00:03:37,045
Black car with flashing lights?

27
00:03:37,685 --> 00:03:38,565
Yes. I see you.

28
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:46,965
What?

29
00:03:52,685 --> 00:03:53,725
Can I help you, miss?

30
00:03:54,325 --> 00:03:55,885
Why did you pick someone else up?

31
00:03:55,965 --> 00:03:57,205
I didn't order a shared ride.

32
00:03:59,285 --> 00:04:00,565
Whatever. It doesn't matter.

33
00:04:00,645 --> 00:04:02,125
Drop me off first. I'm in a rush.

34
00:04:02,805 --> 00:04:03,725
Please scoot over.

35
00:04:10,205 --> 00:04:11,045
Sir?

36
00:04:12,125 --> 00:04:13,645
Are you sure you want to get in?

37
00:04:30,805 --> 00:04:32,125
Lingyun Hotel, please.

38
00:04:39,405 --> 00:04:41,925
Just relax. If you get me there on time,

39
00:04:42,005 --> 00:04:43,245
I won't give you a bad review.

40
00:04:43,805 --> 00:04:45,245
I know how hard your job is.

41
00:04:46,645 --> 00:04:47,645
Right, sir?

42
00:05:18,845 --> 00:05:20,485
CHU YAN CALLING

43
00:05:22,245 --> 00:05:24,485
<i>Ling, weren't you supposed to pick me up?</i>

44
00:05:24,725 --> 00:05:25,685
<i>Where are you?</i>

45
00:05:29,445 --> 00:05:30,965
Something came up. I ran out of time.

46
00:05:31,045 --> 00:05:35,205
I'm on your commercial castings committee.

47
00:05:35,645 --> 00:05:38,725
I turned down
a luxury car company for you.

48
00:05:39,245 --> 00:05:41,205
<i>Now I'm standing on the street alone.</i>

49
00:05:41,285 --> 00:05:43,045
<i>Is your heart made of stone?</i>

50
00:05:43,645 --> 00:05:44,485
You can take a taxi.

51
00:05:46,845 --> 00:05:49,525
<i>Do famous people like me take taxis?</i>

52
00:05:54,925 --> 00:05:56,485
Hello? Hello?

53
00:06:05,405 --> 00:06:06,245
Hurry up!

54
00:06:09,885 --> 00:06:12,925
Have we met somewhere before?

55
00:06:13,325 --> 00:06:14,285
I've seen you before.

56
00:06:17,845 --> 00:06:20,925
Miss, the way you flirt is out of style.

57
00:06:25,245 --> 00:06:28,845
When we feel like
we've seen something before,

58
00:06:29,485 --> 00:06:30,765
it's called déjà vu.

59
00:06:31,805 --> 00:06:33,725
I feel like I've seen you before, too.

60
00:06:34,685 --> 00:06:37,245
Have you watched <i>The Comical Office</i>
or <i>Story of the Moon?</i>

61
00:06:37,765 --> 00:06:39,725
I was in Episode 36,
around the 24th minute.

62
00:06:39,805 --> 00:06:41,405
I was the maid who got poisoned and died.

63
00:06:41,805 --> 00:06:43,085
That show was so popular.

64
00:06:43,165 --> 00:06:46,045
I'm sorry. I don't watch much TV.

65
00:06:57,405 --> 00:06:59,405
-Hello?
-<i>Are you downstairs yet?</i>

66
00:06:59,485 --> 00:07:00,845
<i>I've been waiting for 10 minutes.</i>

67
00:07:02,765 --> 00:07:03,765
Wrong number?

68
00:07:03,845 --> 00:07:06,285
<i>Didn't you request</i>
<i>a ride to Lingyun Hotel?</i>

69
00:07:07,565 --> 00:07:09,765
But I'm already in a car right now.

70
00:07:09,845 --> 00:07:11,525
<i>I'm still outside the entrance of Tianyi.</i>

71
00:07:12,725 --> 00:07:14,725
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

72
00:07:15,765 --> 00:07:16,605
<i>Ma'am?</i>

73
00:07:17,485 --> 00:07:18,325
<i>Hello?</i>

74
00:07:22,965 --> 00:07:24,845
You're not a cab driver?

75
00:07:27,645 --> 00:07:31,605
This isn't a shared ride?

76
00:07:31,965 --> 00:07:35,885
Did anyone in this car say
it was a shared ride?

77
00:07:36,845 --> 00:07:38,645
I'm so sorry. I got in the wrong car.

78
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:41,045
You can just stop
at the intersection there.

79
00:07:41,285 --> 00:07:42,445
It's OK.

80
00:07:43,765 --> 00:07:45,285
We're going to Lingyun Hotel, too.

81
00:07:45,805 --> 00:07:46,765
What a coincidence.

82
00:07:49,205 --> 00:07:52,085
Sorry about all the trouble.

83
00:08:21,245 --> 00:08:23,005
Thank you for the ride.

84
00:08:23,325 --> 00:08:25,325
I'd be late for casting
if it weren't for you.

85
00:08:25,885 --> 00:08:27,405
-What for?
-A Lingshi Group commercial.

86
00:08:28,805 --> 00:08:29,805
Let's go in.

87
00:08:32,965 --> 00:08:34,005
Hold on.

88
00:08:34,925 --> 00:08:36,165
I think my...

89
00:08:36,245 --> 00:08:39,245
My contact lens fell onto your jacket.

90
00:08:40,085 --> 00:08:41,285
Where is it?

91
00:08:46,085 --> 00:08:47,684
Never mind.

92
00:08:47,765 --> 00:08:49,645
I'm going to be late. Thank you. Bye.

93
00:08:57,405 --> 00:08:58,365
Ling Yizhou!

94
00:09:00,205 --> 00:09:01,285
Who's that woman?

95
00:09:02,085 --> 00:09:03,765
-I don't know.
-You don't know her?

96
00:09:03,845 --> 00:09:05,125
Why was she in your car then?

97
00:09:05,205 --> 00:09:07,165
Why would she get so close to you?

98
00:09:07,725 --> 00:09:10,605
Is that hussy
the reason you didn't pick me up?

99
00:09:12,965 --> 00:09:15,285
Alright, I get it.

100
00:09:16,085 --> 00:09:18,565
Out with the old, in with the new, right?

101
00:09:19,445 --> 00:09:22,765
Women are always
throwing themselves at you.

102
00:09:23,085 --> 00:09:25,565
But don't you worry.
I'll always be by your side.

103
00:09:25,925 --> 00:09:28,885
I'll always keep an eye on you.

104
00:09:29,205 --> 00:09:31,045
-Let go.
-Nope.

105
00:09:32,725 --> 00:09:33,565
Let go.

106
00:09:33,645 --> 00:09:34,565
Nope.

107
00:09:36,245 --> 00:09:37,205
Cut.

108
00:09:38,325 --> 00:09:39,205
So who is she?

109
00:09:40,845 --> 00:09:42,045
She got into the wrong car.

110
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:48,925
Best Actor, huh?

111
00:09:50,165 --> 00:09:51,005
You are amazing.

112
00:09:54,285 --> 00:09:55,125
Thanks.

113
00:09:57,805 --> 00:09:59,725
Hello, my name is Xia Lin.

114
00:09:59,965 --> 00:10:04,125
I graduated from the film academy
and I'm represented by Tianyi.

115
00:10:05,005 --> 00:10:05,845
Tianyi?

116
00:10:06,445 --> 00:10:07,285
Yes.

117
00:10:07,365 --> 00:10:09,405
Mr. Chu, you two are
from the same company.

118
00:10:10,245 --> 00:10:11,085
Are we?

119
00:10:13,685 --> 00:10:14,925
Then you should watch out.

120
00:10:15,605 --> 00:10:18,205
Tianyi only represents the elite.

121
00:10:22,245 --> 00:10:24,445
Alright, which projects have you been in?

122
00:10:25,325 --> 00:10:28,405
I've only had a few small roles
on TV shows before.

123
00:10:29,125 --> 00:10:33,485
I wanted to hone my basic skills,
so I focused more on school.

124
00:10:33,885 --> 00:10:36,205
I've acted in a lot of plays.

125
00:10:37,365 --> 00:10:38,205
That's great.

126
00:10:38,725 --> 00:10:40,645
Let's see how well
you know the basics then.

127
00:10:43,325 --> 00:10:45,885
Have you seen <i>Flirting Scholar</i>?

128
00:10:46,205 --> 00:10:47,765
Of course, Mr. Chu.

129
00:10:48,445 --> 00:10:51,125
Do you want me to act as Chow Heung?

130
00:10:52,045 --> 00:10:57,645
No, I want you to act
as the stunningly... ugly one.

131
00:11:06,765 --> 00:11:08,645
"Everyone knows you're
secretly in love with me.

132
00:11:08,725 --> 00:11:11,165
How can I live like this? I'd rather die."

133
00:11:11,685 --> 00:11:14,645
"That's not true.
I love you like my mother."

134
00:11:15,765 --> 00:11:17,765
"You're in love with
your own mother? Gosh.

135
00:11:18,285 --> 00:11:20,805
These morally depraved things you do

136
00:11:20,885 --> 00:11:22,205
really turn me on.

137
00:11:23,205 --> 00:11:25,325
I've never tried this before.
I'm a bit nervous.

138
00:11:25,965 --> 00:11:27,605
Come on. Hurry up."

139
00:11:28,205 --> 00:11:29,365
-Stop.
-"Come on."

140
00:11:29,445 --> 00:11:30,605
Cut!

141
00:11:42,045 --> 00:11:43,085
You did pretty well.

142
00:11:45,245 --> 00:11:47,765
You'd be great
as the female lead in the commercial.

143
00:11:48,445 --> 00:11:51,125
I hope we'll see you again in the future.

144
00:11:51,805 --> 00:11:52,885
Thank you, Mr. Chu.

145
00:11:52,965 --> 00:11:53,965
That's all for today.

146
00:12:02,325 --> 00:12:03,485
Mr. Chu,

147
00:12:04,165 --> 00:12:05,285
my friend really likes you.

148
00:12:05,805 --> 00:12:07,805
Could I get your autograph for her?

149
00:12:09,045 --> 00:12:10,685
Sure. No problem.

150
00:12:11,925 --> 00:12:14,645
My friend's name is Jia Fei. J-I-A, F-E-I.

151
00:12:24,045 --> 00:12:25,845
How did I offend him?

152
00:12:26,605 --> 00:12:28,325
That was the first time we met.

153
00:12:32,365 --> 00:12:33,365
Hello.

154
00:12:36,285 --> 00:12:37,685
Hello. What would you like to order?

155
00:12:38,245 --> 00:12:39,245
Two black coffees.

156
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:43,045
-Hello?
<i>-They chose a female lead for the ad.</i>

157
00:12:44,085 --> 00:12:46,125
That fast? Did I get it?

158
00:12:52,765 --> 00:12:53,605
Lisa,

159
00:12:53,965 --> 00:12:56,405
I'll keep working hard.

160
00:13:01,485 --> 00:13:04,925
I thought I did well.
Why didn't they pick me?

161
00:13:15,765 --> 00:13:17,445
Linlin, why are you home so early?

162
00:13:17,525 --> 00:13:18,885
I'm glad you're home.

163
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:20,325
I got some food for you.

164
00:13:21,725 --> 00:13:24,445
I need to get to the office. Come with me.

165
00:13:24,525 --> 00:13:26,045
Let me rest for a bit.

166
00:13:26,125 --> 00:13:28,325
The casting didn't go well for me today.

167
00:13:35,285 --> 00:13:36,285
Who are you?

168
00:13:37,125 --> 00:13:38,005
Qin Jing?

169
00:13:38,085 --> 00:13:39,405
-Linlin, let me explain.
-Let go.

170
00:13:39,725 --> 00:13:40,725
Explain? How?

171
00:13:41,085 --> 00:13:43,925
Xia Lin, Jia Yan has wanted to dump you
for a long time.

172
00:13:44,605 --> 00:13:45,525
Handle this with grace,

173
00:13:46,365 --> 00:13:47,845
so things won't be too awkward.

174
00:13:48,805 --> 00:13:49,965
Stop talking.

175
00:13:50,845 --> 00:13:53,405
My college friend stole my boyfriend,

176
00:13:53,925 --> 00:13:55,205
and it's my own fault?

177
00:13:55,565 --> 00:13:56,485
What do you want then?

178
00:13:56,965 --> 00:13:58,045
What do I want?

179
00:13:59,125 --> 00:14:01,725
It must have been hard for you
to keep this from me.

180
00:14:02,525 --> 00:14:04,565
If you like him, he's all yours.

181
00:14:05,045 --> 00:14:06,005
I'm tired of him.

182
00:14:06,685 --> 00:14:08,365
-Linlin.
-Don't go after her!

183
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:15,085
Cheaters deserve to be together. Have fun.

184
00:14:27,245 --> 00:14:28,645
I'll pick you up soon.

185
00:14:31,165 --> 00:14:32,165
Excuse me, miss.

186
00:14:32,245 --> 00:14:34,085
I'm about to go and pick up my girlfriend.

187
00:14:34,645 --> 00:14:35,685
Girlfriend?

188
00:14:36,205 --> 00:14:38,285
Now that you're in love,
you don't need to work.

189
00:14:38,365 --> 00:14:40,685
How do you know
she won't dump you or cheat on you?

190
00:14:40,765 --> 00:14:42,965
If you can't be sure,
why not drive me home first?

191
00:14:51,925 --> 00:14:52,765
Crazy.

192
00:14:55,445 --> 00:14:57,925
I'm an actress. I'm a future star.

193
00:14:58,445 --> 00:14:59,485
I have to look like a star.

194
00:15:01,885 --> 00:15:03,165
<i>Keep looking like a star.</i>

195
00:15:21,725 --> 00:15:24,885
Miss Xia,
leukemia isn't an incurable disease.

196
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:26,485
If you start treatment early

197
00:15:26,565 --> 00:15:30,245
and find a bone marrow donor,
then your chances are good.

198
00:15:31,325 --> 00:15:34,445
You should call your family
and do a follow-up right away.

199
00:17:04,045 --> 00:17:08,725
GANGDONG INTERNATIONAL MEDICAL CENTER

200
00:17:09,005 --> 00:17:09,965
Yizhou...

201
00:17:10,965 --> 00:17:13,885
your mom called me yesterday.

202
00:17:17,925 --> 00:17:19,565
It's been so many years,

203
00:17:19,805 --> 00:17:21,045
you still can't forgive her?

204
00:17:22,765 --> 00:17:24,645
Does my forgiveness matter to her?

205
00:17:25,405 --> 00:17:28,765
She left me. She means nothing to me now.

206
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:33,725
Alright. We don't need to talk about her.

207
00:17:34,605 --> 00:17:38,205
Chu Yan said An Ran is coming home
after she graduates.

208
00:17:39,245 --> 00:17:40,285
Really?

209
00:17:40,805 --> 00:17:42,125
Don't act like I'm stupid.

210
00:17:42,885 --> 00:17:45,485
You've been single for years.
You're waiting for her.

211
00:17:46,125 --> 00:17:47,645
Grandma, it's not like that.

212
00:17:48,565 --> 00:17:49,805
An Ran is like a sister to me.

213
00:17:50,405 --> 00:17:51,845
A sister?

214
00:17:53,325 --> 00:17:56,405
Could it be that you
actually like Chu Yan?

215
00:17:57,485 --> 00:17:58,605
Grandma.

216
00:17:59,685 --> 00:18:03,645
I know you don't trust people
because of your mom.

217
00:18:04,245 --> 00:18:06,965
But I'm old. I won't be around forever.

218
00:18:07,285 --> 00:18:11,165
I want you to have someone
who will love and cherish you.

219
00:18:11,645 --> 00:18:13,205
Or else I'll always worry about you.

220
00:18:14,125 --> 00:18:16,885
I'll like anyone you choose.

221
00:18:19,645 --> 00:18:22,205
But if you choose Chu Yan...

222
00:18:22,285 --> 00:18:24,565
would he be my daughter-in-law
or my grandson?

223
00:18:24,965 --> 00:18:25,845
Grandma,

224
00:18:26,485 --> 00:18:27,565
don't worry so much.

225
00:18:28,525 --> 00:18:29,925
I'll start thinking about marriage.

226
00:18:31,085 --> 00:18:32,045
You have a girlfriend?

227
00:18:34,725 --> 00:18:35,565
Kind of.

228
00:18:35,965 --> 00:18:37,125
What do you mean, "kind of"?

229
00:18:37,205 --> 00:18:38,805
Either you do or you don't.

230
00:18:39,405 --> 00:18:43,165
Do you not have time to date
because of work?

231
00:18:43,405 --> 00:18:45,085
Tell me what's going on.
I'll help you out.

232
00:18:45,845 --> 00:18:47,165
Grandma, I know what you mean.

233
00:18:48,325 --> 00:18:49,405
That's all that matters.

234
00:18:50,565 --> 00:18:54,085
Miss Xia, I'm sorry to inform you
that your diagnosis has been confirmed.

235
00:18:59,645 --> 00:19:01,365
There's only one way to cure leukemia...

236
00:19:01,925 --> 00:19:03,165
A stem cell transplant.

237
00:19:04,005 --> 00:19:06,485
We don't have any matches
in the donor registry right now.

238
00:19:06,885 --> 00:19:08,765
All we can do
is try to control it with drugs.

239
00:19:11,485 --> 00:19:12,485
So, what you mean is...

240
00:19:14,605 --> 00:19:15,605
chemotherapy?

241
00:19:16,365 --> 00:19:17,205
That's right.

242
00:19:23,365 --> 00:19:24,605
So, I'll end up...

243
00:19:26,325 --> 00:19:28,205
losing all my hair, right?

244
00:19:30,165 --> 00:19:31,445
I'll have diarrhea, too.

245
00:19:33,325 --> 00:19:34,885
I'll be so ugly.

246
00:19:37,045 --> 00:19:39,885
I won't be able to act anymore, right?

247
00:19:40,645 --> 00:19:41,605
Once you get better...

248
00:19:43,005 --> 00:19:44,725
you'll be able to do
whatever job you like.

249
00:19:46,485 --> 00:19:47,645
You'll be like...

250
00:19:48,565 --> 00:19:50,445
that American celebrity,

251
00:19:50,965 --> 00:19:51,965
Selena Gomez.

252
00:19:53,605 --> 00:19:57,765
She's been just as amazing
since she got a new kidney.

253
00:19:58,365 --> 00:19:59,525
Don't lose hope.

254
00:19:59,885 --> 00:20:01,925
Maybe you'll find a match very soon.

255
00:20:03,125 --> 00:20:04,405
Don't lie to me.

256
00:20:05,925 --> 00:20:07,165
I looked it up online.

257
00:20:09,085 --> 00:20:12,325
The chances of finding
a matching bone marrow donor are low.

258
00:20:19,325 --> 00:20:20,165
Doctor...

259
00:20:22,125 --> 00:20:24,245
is there something else
you aren't telling me?

260
00:20:24,965 --> 00:20:29,205
We did find a match
in the bone marrow registry...

261
00:20:31,885 --> 00:20:33,805
but this person
isn't willing to donate now.

262
00:20:34,685 --> 00:20:35,765
